CREATE (:ContentChunk {id: 'lamad-reference-implementation__chunk_0', parentId: 'lamad-reference-implementation', chunkIndex: 0, totalChunks: 2, content: '# Lamad: A Reference Implementation of the Elohim Protocol{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## What Is Lamad?{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Lamad** (לָמַד, Hebrew: {{DQUOTE}}to learn{{DQUOTE}}) is a reference implementation demonstrating how the Elohim Protocol principles can be embodied in software. It is not an epic of the protocol—it is a working example of how any developer can build applications that serve human flourishing rather than extract from it.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Lamad transforms learning from content consumption into meaning-making. Where traditional platforms ask {{DQUOTE}}did you complete the module?{{DQUOTE}}, Lamad asks {{DQUOTE}}how does this change what you understand about yourself and the world?{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Why a Reference Implementation?{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The Elohim Protocol is a vision—a set of principles for digital infrastructure that serves human flourishing. But principles alone don{{QUOTE}}t build software. Developers need patterns, architectures, and working examples.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Lamad provides:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}1. **Concrete Architecture**: How to structure knowledge as a graph rather than content silos{{NEWLINE}}2. **Design Patterns**: Services, models, and data structures that embody protocol principles{{NEWLINE}}3. **Working Code**: An Angular application demonstrating these patterns in action{{NEWLINE}}4. **Integration Points**: How to connect with Elohim agents for content synthesis{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Core Architectural Principles{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 1. Territory vs. Journey (ContentNode vs. PathStep){{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**The Distinction:**{{NEWLINE}}- **Territory (ContentNode)**: A piece of knowledge that exists independently—a concept, a resource, a perspective. It is *reusable* across contexts.{{NEWLINE}}- **Journey (PathStep)**: A narrative moment in a learning path that references territory. It provides *context* for encountering that territory.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Why This Matters:**{{NEWLINE}}Traditional LMS systems conflate content with courses. A video exists only within its course. Lamad separates them:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}ContentNode: {{DQUOTE}}Deep Work by Cal Newport{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  - Exists once in the graph{{NEWLINE}}  - Has its own metadata, tags, relationships{{NEWLINE}}  - Can be encountered from multiple paths{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}PathStep in {{DQUOTE}}Foundations for Christian Technology{{DQUOTE}}:{{NEWLINE}}  - References {{DQUOTE}}Deep Work{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  - Provides context: {{DQUOTE}}Consider how sacred attention relates to focused work{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  - Tracks this human{{QUOTE}}s specific engagement{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}PathStep in {{DQUOTE}}Productivity for Creators{{DQUOTE}}:{{NEWLINE}}  - References same {{DQUOTE}}Deep Work{{DQUOTE}} node{{NEWLINE}}  - Different context: {{DQUOTE}}Technical practices for deep concentration{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  - Same content, different narrative{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**The Implementation:**{{NEWLINE}}```typescript{{NEWLINE}}// ContentNode - the territory{{NEWLINE}}interface ContentNode {{{NEWLINE}}  id: string;{{NEWLINE}}  contentType: {{QUOTE}}article{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}video{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}book{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}concept{{QUOTE}} | ...;{{NEWLINE}}  title: string;{{NEWLINE}}  content: any;  // Flexible based on contentType{{NEWLINE}}  tags: string[];{{NEWLINE}}  relatedNodeIds: string[];  // Graph connections{{NEWLINE}}}{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}// PathStep - the journey moment{{NEWLINE}}interface PathStep {{{NEWLINE}}  order: number;{{NEWLINE}}  stepType: {{QUOTE}}content{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}path{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}checkpoint{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}external{{QUOTE}};{{NEWLINE}}  resourceId: string;  // References ContentNode.id{{NEWLINE}}  stepTitle?: string;  // Narrative framing for this encounter{{NEWLINE}}  stepDescription?: string;{{NEWLINE}}  sharedConcepts?: string[];  // Bridges to other content{{NEWLINE}}}{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 2. Graph-Based Knowledge Architecture{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**The Problem with Hierarchies:**{{NEWLINE}}Traditional platforms force content into rigid hierarchies: Course > Module > Lesson. But knowledge doesn{{QUOTE}}t work that way. Concepts connect across domains. A lesson on {{DQUOTE}}systems thinking{{DQUOTE}} relates to governance, economics, ecology, psychology—not just its parent course.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Lamad{{QUOTE}}s Graph Model:**{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}┌─────────────┐         ┌─────────────┐{{NEWLINE}}│  Concept:   │─────────│  Concept:   │{{NEWLINE}}│  Systems    │ RELATES │  Feedback   │{{NEWLINE}}│  Thinking   │─────────│  Loops      │{{NEWLINE}}└──────┬──────┘         └──────┬──────┘{{NEWLINE}}       │                       │{{NEWLINE}}  REFERENCED_BY           REFERENCED_BY{{NEWLINE}}       │                       │{{NEWLINE}}┌──────┴──────┐         ┌──────┴──────┐{{NEWLINE}}│ FCT Module 2│         │ Governance  │{{NEWLINE}}│ Complex vs  │         │ Elohim as   │{{NEWLINE}}│ Complicated │         │ Negotiators │{{NEWLINE}}└─────────────┘         └─────────────┘{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Relationship Types:**{{NEWLINE}}- `CONTAINS` - Structural containment (path contains steps){{NEWLINE}}- `REFERENCES` - Content references another node{{NEWLINE}}- `CREATED_BY` - Attribution to contributor{{NEWLINE}}- `PUBLISHED_BY` - Attribution to organization{{NEWLINE}}- `CONCEPTUALLY_RELATED` - Semantic connection{{NEWLINE}}- `BUILDS_ON` - Prerequisite relationship{{NEWLINE}}- `CONTRASTS_WITH` - Opposing perspective{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 3. Affinity, Not Mastery{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**The Problem with {{DQUOTE}}Mastery{{DQUOTE}}:**{{NEWLINE}}Traditional learning platforms treat knowledge as something to be *conquered*. You {{DQUOTE}}master{{DQUOTE}} a skill, {{DQUOTE}}complete{{DQUOTE}} a course, achieve {{DQUOTE}}100%{{DQUOTE}}. This model:{{NEWLINE}}- Reduces learning to checkboxes{{NEWLINE}}- Implies knowledge has an endpoint{{NEWLINE}}- Ignores the depth dimension of understanding{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Lamad{{QUOTE}}s Affinity Model:**{{NEWLINE}}Affinity measures *relationship depth* between a human and a concept—not whether they{{QUOTE}}ve {{DQUOTE}}completed{{DQUOTE}} something.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}```typescript{{NEWLINE}}interface AffinityRecord {{{NEWLINE}}  humanId: string;{{NEWLINE}}  nodeId: string;{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}  // Engagement depth (not completion){{NEWLINE}}  engagementScore: number;  // 0-100, accumulated through interaction{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}  // Qualitative indicators{{NEWLINE}}  hasEngaged: boolean;{{NEWLINE}}  hasReflected: boolean;  // Meaningful pause/note{{NEWLINE}}  hasConnected: boolean;  // Drew connections to other concepts{{NEWLINE}}  hasApplied: boolean;    // Used in real context{{NEWLINE}}  hasShared: boolean;     // Taught or discussed with others{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}  // Temporal dimension{{NEWLINE}}  firstEncounter: Date;{{NEWLINE}}  lastEncounter: Date;{{NEWLINE}}  encounterCount: number;{{NEWLINE}}}{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Why Affinity Matters:**{{NEWLINE}}When you engage with {{DQUOTE}}Deep Work{{DQUOTE}} in one path, your affinity with that concept carries to other paths. You don{{QUOTE}}t {{DQUOTE}}re-complete{{DQUOTE}} it—but encountering it in a new context deepens your relationship with the idea.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 4. Attestation-Gated Progression{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Not Credentials, Relationships:**{{NEWLINE}}Traditional platforms issue credentials: {{DQUOTE}}Certificate of Completion.{{DQUOTE}} These are transactional—you did the work, you get the paper.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Lamad uses **attestations**—statements about your relationship with knowledge that enable new possibilities.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}```typescript{{NEWLINE}}interface Attestation {{{NEWLINE}}  id: string;{{NEWLINE}}  type: {{QUOTE}}engagement{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}reflection{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}application{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}teaching{{QUOTE}};{{NEWLINE}}  nodeId: string;  // What this attests to{{NEWLINE}}  humanId: string;{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}  // The attestation itself{{NEWLINE}}  statement: string;  // {{DQUOTE}}Has deeply engaged with systems thinking{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  evidence?: string;  // Optional supporting material{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}  // What this enables{{NEWLINE}}  enablesAccess?: string[];  // Paths now available{{NEWLINE}}  enablesRole?: string[];    // Community roles unlocked{{NEWLINE}}}{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Gating Examples:**{{NEWLINE}}- {{DQUOTE}}Governance Deep Dive{{DQUOTE}} path requires attestation of engagement with manifesto{{NEWLINE}}- {{DQUOTE}}Teaching Assistant{{DQUOTE}} role requires attestation of having taught others{{NEWLINE}}- {{DQUOTE}}Constitutional Council{{DQUOTE}} participation requires attestations from multiple domains{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 5. Three Meaning Maps{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Lamad enables three types of maps that emerge from graph relationships:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Human → Subject (Knowledge Map):**{{NEWLINE}}*{{DQUOTE}}What do I know about this topic?{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}Your engagement with {{DQUOTE}}Systems Thinking{{DQUOTE}}:{{NEWLINE}}├── First encountered: FCT Module 2{{NEWLINE}}├── Deepened through: Governance Epic{{NEWLINE}}├── Connected to: Feedback Loops, Complex Adaptive Systems{{NEWLINE}}├── Applied in: Your community project proposal{{NEWLINE}}└── Affinity: 78% (deep engagement, not {{DQUOTE}}complete{{DQUOTE}}){{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Human → Human (Love Map):**{{NEWLINE}}*{{DQUOTE}}How does my understanding overlap with others?{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}You and Sarah both engaged with:{{NEWLINE}}├── {{DQUOTE}}The Ministry for the Future{{DQUOTE}} (different chapters){{NEWLINE}}├── Governance Epic (similar affinity){{NEWLINE}}├── Systems Thinking (complementary perspectives){{NEWLINE}}└── Suggested: Discuss regenerative economics together{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Human → Self (Self Map):**{{NEWLINE}}*{{DQUOTE}}What patterns exist in my learning?{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}Your Learning Patterns:{{NEWLINE}}├── Strong: Systems thinking, ethical frameworks, community design{{NEWLINE}}├── Growing: Technical implementation, economic coordination{{NEWLINE}}├── Gap: Care economics, value measurement{{NEWLINE}}├── Suggested: Explore ValueFlows to round out understanding{{NEWLINE}}└── Emerging Theme: You gravitate toward whole-systems approaches{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Technical Architecture{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Service Layer{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐{{NEWLINE}}│                      Lamad Services                          │{{NEWLINE}}├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤{{NEWLINE}}│                                                              │{{NEWLINE}}│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │   Content    │  │   Learning   │  │   Graph      │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │   Service    │  │   Path       │  │   Service    │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │              │  │   Service    │  │              │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │ - Load nodes │  │ - Get paths  │  │ - Query      │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │ - Query by   │  │ - Track      │  │   relationships│     │{{NEWLINE}}│  │   category   │  │   progress   │  │ - Find       │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │ - Get related│  │ - Get next   │  │   connections │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘       │{{NEWLINE}}│                                                              │{{NEWLINE}}│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │   Affinity   │  │   Elohim     │  │   Assessment │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │   Tracking   │  │   Agent      │  │   Service    │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │   Service    │  │   Service    │  │              │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │              │  │              │  │ - Personal   │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │ - Track      │  │ - Content    │  │   values     │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │   engagement │  │   synthesis  │  │ - Strengths  │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │ - Calculate  │  │ - Path       │  │ - Reflection │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  │   affinity   │  │   generation │  │   prompts    │       │{{NEWLINE}}│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘       │{{NEWLINE}}│                                                              │{{NEWLINE}}└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Data Layer (JSON-based for Reference Implementation){{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}/assets/lamad-data/{{NEWLINE}}├── content/                    # ContentNodes{{NEWLINE}}│   ├── index.json             # Content index{{NEWLINE}}│   ├── [node-id].json         # Individual content files{{NEWLINE}}│   └── ...{{NEWLINE}}├── paths/                      # LearningPaths{{NEWLINE}}│   ├── index.json             # Path index{{NEWLINE}}│   ├── [path-id].json         # Individual path files{{NEWLINE}}│   └── ...{{NEWLINE}}├── graph/                      # Relationships{{NEWLINE}}│   ├── relationships.json     # All graph edges{{NEWLINE}}│   ├── epic-[name].json      # Epic-specific subgraphs{{NEWLINE}}│   └── overview.json          # High-level structure{{NEWLINE}}├── assessments/               # Self-knowledge tools{{NEWLINE}}│   └── ...{{NEWLINE}}└── knowledge-maps/            # Personal maps (user-specific){{NEWLINE}}    └── ...{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Model Definitions{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}```typescript{{NEWLINE}}// Core content model{{NEWLINE}}interface ContentNode {{{NEWLINE}}  id: string;{{NEWLINE}}  contentType: ContentType;{{NEWLINE}}  title: string;{{NEWLINE}}  description: string;{{NEWLINE}}  content: any;{{NEWLINE}}  contentFormat: string;{{NEWLINE}}  sourcePath?: string;{{NEWLINE}}  tags: string[];{{NEWLINE}}  relatedNodeIds: string[];{{NEWLINE}}  metadata: Record<string, any>;{{NEWLINE}}  createdAt: string;{{NEWLINE}}  updatedAt: string;{{NEWLINE}}}{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}// Learning path model{{NEWLINE}}interface LearningPath {{{NEWLINE}}  id: string;{{NEWLINE}}  title: string;{{NEWLINE}}  description: string;{{NEWLINE}}  pathType?: {{QUOTE}}journey{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}quest{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}expedition{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}practice{{QUOTE}};{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}  // Structure (use ONE of these){{NEWLINE}}  steps: PathStep[];           // Flat sequence{{NEWLINE}}  chapters?: PathChapter[];    // Thematic groupings{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}  // Gating and rewards{{NEWLINE}}  prerequisites?: string[];{{NEWLINE}}  attestationsRequired?: string[];{{NEWLINE}}  attestationsGranted?: string[];{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}  metadata: {{{NEWLINE}}    category?: string;{{NEWLINE}}    estimatedDuration?: string;{{NEWLINE}}    difficulty?: {{QUOTE}}foundational{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}intermediate{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}advanced{{QUOTE}};{{NEWLINE}}    themes?: string[];{{NEWLINE}}  };{{NEWLINE}}}{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}// Path step model (journey moment){{NEWLINE}}interface PathStep {{{NEWLINE}}  order: number;{{NEWLINE}}  stepType?: {{QUOTE}}content{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}path{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}external{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}checkpoint{{QUOTE}};{{NEWLINE}}  resourceId: string;{{NEWLINE}}  pathId?: string;  // For stepType: {{QUOTE}}path{{QUOTE}} (composition){{NEWLINE}}  stepTitle?: string;{{NEWLINE}}  stepDescription?: string;{{NEWLINE}}  checkpointPrompt?: string;  // For reflection moments{{NEWLINE}}  sharedConcepts?: string[];  // Bridges to other content{{NEWLINE}}}{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}// Contributor presence model{{NEWLINE}}interface ContributorPresence {{{NEWLINE}}  id: string;{{NEWLINE}}  contentType: {{QUOTE}}contributor{{QUOTE}};{{NEWLINE}}  title: string;  // Person{{QUOTE}}s name{{NEWLINE}}  content: {{{NEWLINE}}    name: string;{{NEWLINE}}    role: {{QUOTE}}author{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}speaker{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}filmmaker{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}researcher{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}creator{{QUOTE}};{{NEWLINE}}    works: string[];{{NEWLINE}}    bio?: string;{{NEWLINE}}  };{{NEWLINE}}  status: {{QUOTE}}unclaimed{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}stewarded{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}claimed{{QUOTE}};{{NEWLINE}}  relatedNodeIds: string[];{{NEWLINE}}}{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## The {{DQUOTE}}Exit with Elohim{{DQUOTE}} Capability{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Vision: Content Synthesis{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}'});
CREATE (:ContentChunk {id: 'lamad-reference-implementation__chunk_1', parentId: 'lamad-reference-implementation', chunkIndex: 1, totalChunks: 2, content: 'What Lamad demonstrates manually through data generation scripts, an Elohim agent should do automatically:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}Human: {{DQUOTE}}Here{{QUOTE}}s a book I want to learn from{{DQUOTE}} [uploads PDF]{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Elohim Agent:{{NEWLINE}}1. Parses content structure (chapters, sections, key concepts){{NEWLINE}}2. Extracts entities (people, organizations, references){{NEWLINE}}3. Identifies learning objectives{{NEWLINE}}4. Maps concepts to existing knowledge graph{{NEWLINE}}5. Discovers shared meaning with content the human already knows{{NEWLINE}}6. Generates personalized learning path{{NEWLINE}}7. Creates ContributorPresence nodes for unclaimed authors{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### The Transformation Process{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Input**: Unstructured content (PDF, URL, notes, video transcript){{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Step 1 - Decomposition**:{{NEWLINE}}- Structure: Chapters, sections, hierarchy{{NEWLINE}}- Concepts: Key ideas, themes, arguments{{NEWLINE}}- Entities: People, organizations, references{{NEWLINE}}- Media: Videos, books, articles mentioned{{NEWLINE}}- Learning objectives: What this content teaches{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Step 2 - Graph Integration**:{{NEWLINE}}- Find overlapping concepts with existing nodes{{NEWLINE}}- Identify related content human has engaged with{{NEWLINE}}- Create new nodes for novel concepts{{NEWLINE}}- Establish relationships{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Step 3 - Path Generation**:{{NEWLINE}}- Leverage existing knowledge (don{{QUOTE}}t re-teach){{NEWLINE}}- Fill gaps in understanding{{NEWLINE}}- Connect to human{{QUOTE}}s interests/goals{{NEWLINE}}- Sequence for optimal comprehension{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Step 4 - Continuous Refinement**:{{NEWLINE}}- Track affinity as human engages{{NEWLINE}}- Update maps based on new understanding{{NEWLINE}}- Suggest next steps{{NEWLINE}}- Connect with other humans on similar journeys{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Why {{DQUOTE}}Exit with Elohim{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Traditional platforms say: *{{DQUOTE}}Import your content into our system.{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Lamad says: **{{DQUOTE}}Exit with Elohim.{{DQUOTE}}**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Exit from:**{{NEWLINE}}- The extractive attention economy{{NEWLINE}}- Platforms that commodify your learning{{NEWLINE}}- Systems where you{{QUOTE}}re the product{{NEWLINE}}- Siloed knowledge that doesn{{QUOTE}}t connect{{NEWLINE}}- Content that stays inert, never becoming wisdom{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Exit into:**{{NEWLINE}}- The Elohim Protocol network{{NEWLINE}}- A space where your learning belongs to you{{NEWLINE}}- Knowledge that connects to other humans{{NEWLINE}}- Content that becomes living meaning{{NEWLINE}}- Understanding that reveals who you are{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Human-Centered Language{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Throughout Lamad, we use **{{DQUOTE}}human{{DQUOTE}}** rather than {{DQUOTE}}user{{DQUOTE}} intentionally:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}- A **human** has dignity, agency, and a unique learning journey{{NEWLINE}}- A **user** is a consumer of a product{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This isn{{QUOTE}}t semantic posturing—it shapes how we build. When you think {{DQUOTE}}user,{{DQUOTE}} you optimize for engagement metrics. When you think {{DQUOTE}}human,{{DQUOTE}} you design for flourishing.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The Elohim Protocol centers on **Imago Dei**—each human as image-bearer. The technology serves the human{{QUOTE}}s flourishing, not the other way around.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Implementation Guide for Developers{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Starting Points{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}1. **Content Service**: Begin with `ContentService` - loading and querying content nodes{{NEWLINE}}2. **Graph Service**: Implement relationship queries for navigation{{NEWLINE}}3. **Path Service**: Build path rendering and progress tracking{{NEWLINE}}4. **Affinity Service**: Add engagement depth tracking{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Key Design Decisions{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Choose Generic Over Domain-Specific:**{{NEWLINE}}- Use `category` not `primaryEpic`{{NEWLINE}}- Use `attestation` not `skill` or `badge`{{NEWLINE}}- Use `affinity` not `mastery` or `completion`{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Separate Territory from Journey:**{{NEWLINE}}- ContentNode is reusable{{NEWLINE}}- PathStep provides context{{NEWLINE}}- Same content, multiple narratives{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Graph First:**{{NEWLINE}}- Don{{QUOTE}}t force hierarchies{{NEWLINE}}- Let relationships emerge{{NEWLINE}}- Query by connection, not containment{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Human Dignity:**{{NEWLINE}}- No dark patterns{{NEWLINE}}- No engagement manipulation{{NEWLINE}}- Transparent about data use{{NEWLINE}}- Human controls their learning journey{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Extending Lamad{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**New Content Types:**{{NEWLINE}}```typescript{{NEWLINE}}// Add to content-node.model.ts{{NEWLINE}}export type ContentType ={{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}article{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}video{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}book{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}podcast{{QUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}course{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}module{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}quiz{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}assessment{{QUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}reflection{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}practice{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}discussion{{QUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}concept{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}principle{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}story{{QUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}contributor{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}organization{{QUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}your-new-type{{QUOTE}};  // Extend as needed{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**New Relationship Types:**{{NEWLINE}}```typescript{{NEWLINE}}// Add to graph model{{NEWLINE}}export type RelationshipType ={{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}CONTAINS{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}REFERENCES{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}CREATED_BY{{QUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}BUILDS_ON{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}CONTRASTS_WITH{{QUOTE}} | {{QUOTE}}APPLIES_TO{{QUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}  | {{QUOTE}}YOUR_NEW_RELATIONSHIP{{QUOTE}};  // Extend as needed{{NEWLINE}}```{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**New Assessment Types:**{{NEWLINE}}Create assessments in `/assets/lamad-data/assessments/` that help humans understand themselves better—values clarification, strengths identification, learning style discovery.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## What Lamad Proves{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This reference implementation demonstrates that it{{QUOTE}}s possible to:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}1. **Take unstructured educational content** and decompose it into meaningful entities{{NEWLINE}}2. **Create reusable knowledge graphs** where content connects across domains{{NEWLINE}}3. **Enable content reuse** where the same territory appears in multiple journeys{{NEWLINE}}4. **Track relationship depth** (affinity) rather than completion checkboxes{{NEWLINE}}5. **Build attestation-gated progression** that enables rather than credentials{{NEWLINE}}6. **Generate personalized meaning maps** showing human→subject, human→human, human→self{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This is the foundation for **intelligent content synthesis**—where an Elohim agent can take any content a human wants to learn and integrate it into a personalized meaning map that connects them to knowledge, to each other, and to themselves.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Join the Development{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Lamad is open source and welcomes contributions that align with Elohim Protocol principles:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}- **GitHub**: [Repository Link]{{NEWLINE}}- **Documentation**: This document and `/fct/claude.md`{{NEWLINE}}- **Community**: [Community Link]{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Build something that serves human flourishing. Exit with Elohim.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}*{{DQUOTE}}The future is already here—it{{QUOTE}}s just not evenly distributed.{{DQUOTE}}* —William Gibson{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}*{{DQUOTE}}Capable enough intelligence takes unstructured content and decomposes/recomposes it into structure most digestible for each human{{QUOTE}}s flourishing.{{DQUOTE}}* —The Lamad Vision{{NEWLINE}}'});
