CREATE (:ContentChunk {id: 'value-scanner-epic__chunk_0', parentId: 'value-scanner-epic', chunkIndex: 0, totalChunks: 2, content: '# The Elohim Value Scanner: How a Boy Buying Strawberries Changes Everything{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## A Protocol for the Care Economy{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## The Strawberry Revolution{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Tuesday afternoon, 3:45 PM. Ten-year-old Tommy Parker stands in the produce aisle of his neighborhood corner store, holding his phone over a container of strawberries. The phone vibrates gently: *{{DQUOTE}}Emma will love these! +5 care bonus for thinking of sister.{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This simple moment—a child considering his sister while shopping—represents something revolutionary. Not because of the technology involved (it{{QUOTE}}s just a smartphone and QR codes), but because of what it makes visible: care has become computable, valuable, and exchangeable.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Tommy doesn{{QUOTE}}t know he{{QUOTE}}s participating in an economic revolution. He just knows that when he gets home, the family hub will celebrate his contribution, his parents will save 45 minutes, and Emma will smile when she sees the strawberries.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This isn{{QUOTE}}t another payment app charging families monthly fees. It{{QUOTE}}s economic infrastructure that makes care primary value.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## The Hidden Tax on Modern Families{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Before we follow Tommy through his shopping trip, let{{QUOTE}}s talk about what families face today.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### The Monthly Rent on Childhood{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Right now, millions of parents pay $5-15 monthly to apps like Greenlight, FamZoo, and Capital One Teen Banking. These apps promise to teach kids about money. What they actually teach is consumption. They lock families into their ecosystems, extract behavioral data for marketing, and charge rent on the basic act of raising financially literate children.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Consider what parents are actually paying for:{{NEWLINE}}- **Greenlight**: $5-15/month to let kids spend their own money{{NEWLINE}}- **FamZoo**: $2.50-5/month for virtual family banking{{NEWLINE}}- **Acorns Early**: $5/month for kids{{QUOTE}} investment accounts{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}That{{QUOTE}}s up to $300 per year, per family, just for the privilege of teaching kids about money in a digital world. And what do kids learn? That every transaction is surveilled, that spending is the primary economic act, and that value equals dollars.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### The Coordination Burden{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Beyond the financial cost lies a heavier burden: the mental load of family coordination.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The average parent spends 11 hours per week on household management—remembering who needs what, when activities happen, what{{QUOTE}}s in the fridge, who{{QUOTE}}s picking up whom. It{{QUOTE}}s invisible labor that creates visible stress:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}- {{DQUOTE}}Did you remember the milk?{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}- {{DQUOTE}}We have three bottles of ketchup and no mustard.{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}- {{DQUOTE}}I thought you were getting Emma from practice.{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}- {{DQUOTE}}Why didn{{QUOTE}}t you tell me you needed this for tomorrow?{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Current technology hasn{{QUOTE}}t solved this; it{{QUOTE}}s made it worse. Now we coordinate across WhatsApp, shared calendars, shopping apps, banking apps, school apps—each demanding attention, none talking to each other.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Care as Computable Value{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}What if every family interaction—from morning chores to afternoon shopping—could become a moment of value creation through familiar technology?{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Not value extraction. Value creation.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The Elohim Value Scanner (EVS) transforms routine family activities into a rich economy of care, learning, and mutual support. It uses the same devices you already have (smartphones, simple home cameras, QR codes) but with radically different logic: care is the primary currency, money is just one type of value among many.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Here{{QUOTE}}s the revolutionary insight: When care becomes computable, it becomes valuable. When it becomes valuable, it becomes cultivatable. When it becomes cultivatable, it transforms how families function.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## A Day in the Care Economy{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Let{{QUOTE}}s follow the Parker family through a typical Tuesday to see how this works.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 7:00 AM - Morning Recognition{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Tommy enters the kitchen where a small camera observes (never records) the morning routine. He makes breakfast for his six-year-old sister Emma—remembering she doesn{{QUOTE}}t like crusts, using ingredients efficiently, cleaning up without being asked.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The family{{QUOTE}}s Elohim agent, living in their home hub, understands what just happened. On the kitchen display, a gentle notification appears:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Tommy earned:**{{NEWLINE}}- ✨ 10 care tokens (made breakfast for Emma){{NEWLINE}}- ⏰ 15 minute tokens (saved parent time){{NEWLINE}}- 🌱 5 growth tokens (new recipe attempted){{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Tommy doesn{{QUOTE}}t need to log anything. The Elohim observes patterns of care and records the story. This isn{{QUOTE}}t surveillance—the camera sees but doesn{{QUOTE}}t record, understands but doesn{{QUOTE}}t store video. It{{QUOTE}}s like having a wise grandmother who notices when children are kind to each other.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 3:30 PM - The Shopping Mission{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}After school, Tommy checks the family hub. His shopping mission awaits:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Parker Family Mission for Tommy:**{{NEWLINE}}- 📝 Required: Milk, Olive oil{{NEWLINE}}- 💝 Emma{{QUOTE}}s wish: Strawberries  {{NEWLINE}}- 🎯 Discovery budget: $20 for healthy foods{{NEWLINE}}- ⚠️ Remember: No nuts (family allergy){{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This mission assembled itself. The family Elohim noticed milk running low this morning, knows tonight{{QUOTE}}s meal kit needs olive oil, remembered Emma{{QUOTE}}s breakfast request, and added Tommy{{QUOTE}}s learning goal of food discovery. No parent had to make this list. No one had to text reminders.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 3:45 PM - The Shopping Dialogue{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}At the corner store, Tommy uses his phone to scan items. But this isn{{QUOTE}}t self-checkout—it{{QUOTE}}s a conversation between multiple AI agents, each protecting different values while helping Tommy learn.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Tommy scans chips:**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}His phone vibrates gently: *{{DQUOTE}}Treat budget remaining: $3. Baked version available: 20% off with health tokens.{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This isn{{QUOTE}}t judgment. It{{QUOTE}}s information. Tommy can choose the regular chips, the baked ones, or something else entirely. The system guides without controlling.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Tommy scans strawberries:**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}*{{DQUOTE}}Emma will love these! 🍓 Local: Johnson Farm, picked today. +5 care bonus for thinking of sister.{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Now Tommy learns that his thoughtfulness has value, that local farms exist, that food has stories.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Tommy scans expensive olive oil:**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}A negotiation happens in milliseconds:{{NEWLINE}}- Tommy{{QUOTE}}s Elohim: {{DQUOTE}}Over personal budget...{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}- Family Elohim: {{DQUOTE}}But needed for dinner, approving{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}- Community Elohim: {{DQUOTE}}Bulk size better value{{DQUOTE}}  {{NEWLINE}}- Global Elohim: {{DQUOTE}}Mediterranean drought affecting supply{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}- Store Elohim: {{DQUOTE}}Offering 10% discount for bulk{{DQUOTE}}{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Tommy{{QUOTE}}s phone shows: *{{DQUOTE}}Family approved! Get the large size. Saving $3 over time.{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Tommy just participated in a complex economic decision involving family needs, community values, and global supply chains. To him, it felt like getting permission to buy the big bottle.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Tommy approaches the dairy section:**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}A gentle notification: *{{DQUOTE}}Don{{QUOTE}}t forget milk! Mom prefers almond milk.{{DQUOTE}}*{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}No nagging text from mom. No forgotten items. Just gentle support when needed.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 4:15 PM - The Checkout Revolution{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Tommy{{QUOTE}}s basket is already processed. Every scan has been computing in the background. At checkout, he shows a single QR code that contains his entire shopping story. The cashier scans it. Five seconds later, he{{QUOTE}}s done.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}But in those five seconds:{{NEWLINE}}- The store receives payment in dollars{{NEWLINE}}- Tommy{{QUOTE}}s discovery tokens are deducted{{NEWLINE}}- Care tokens are created for thinking of Emma{{NEWLINE}}- Time tokens are credited for saving parents a trip{{NEWLINE}}- Johnson Farm is marked as supported{{NEWLINE}}- Anonymous patterns flow to the community{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This is the **bundle**—the moment where all the micro-negotiations resolve into a single transaction that tells a complete story.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### 6:00 PM - Story Time{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}At dinner, the family hub shows today{{QUOTE}}s story:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**The Parker Family Tuesday**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**TOMMY{{QUOTE}}S CONTRIBUTIONS:**{{NEWLINE}}- Morning: Made Emma breakfast (first time using stove!){{NEWLINE}}- Afternoon: Successful shopping mission{{NEWLINE}}- Values Created: 30 care, 45 time, 15 growth{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**EMMA{{QUOTE}}S CONTRIBUTIONS:**{{NEWLINE}}- Morning: Fed cats without reminder{{NEWLINE}}- Afternoon: Helped neighbor with groceries  {{NEWLINE}}- Values Created: 20 care, 10 community{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**FAMILY WINS:**{{NEWLINE}}- ✓ Everyone contributed{{NEWLINE}}- ✓ Local farm supported{{NEWLINE}}- ✓ No duplicate purchases{{NEWLINE}}- ✓ 90 minutes parent time saved{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This isn{{QUOTE}}t a leaderboard where someone wins and someone loses. It{{QUOTE}}s a celebration of mutual care. Emma sees that Tommy thought of her. Tommy sees that Emma helped the neighbor. Parents see their children growing in compassion.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## The Protocol: How It Actually Works{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The magic happens through a simple protocol loop: **Story → Scan → Negotiate → Bundle → Story**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Phase 1: Story (Morning Planning){{NEWLINE}}The family{{QUOTE}}s needs, values, and constraints aggregate into missions. No spreadsheets, no arguments—just AI agents understanding patterns and creating plans.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Phase 2: Scan (Active Shopping){{NEWLINE}}Each product scan triggers a multi-agent negotiation:{{NEWLINE}}- **Personal Elohim**: Protects individual budget and growth{{NEWLINE}}- **Family Elohim**: Ensures shared needs are met{{NEWLINE}}- **Store Elohim**: Offers deals and information{{NEWLINE}}- **Community Elohim**: Promotes local values{{NEWLINE}}- **Global Elohim**: Provides supply chain awareness{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Phase 3: Negotiate (Real-time Dialogue){{NEWLINE}}Agents reach consensus in milliseconds. Not through rules but through values alignment. Care for sister outweighs treat budget. Family dinner needs override personal limits. Community sustainability shapes choices.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Phase 4: Bundle (Single Checkout){{NEWLINE}}All micro-negotiations resolve into one QR code containing:{{NEWLINE}}- Economic transaction (payments){{NEWLINE}}- Value creation (tokens earned){{NEWLINE}}- Story elements (achievements, care acts){{NEWLINE}}- REA flows (resources, events, agents, commitments){{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Phase 5: Story (Evening Celebration){{NEWLINE}}The day{{QUOTE}}s activities become family narrative. Not data points but stories of care, growth, and contribution.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Progressive Permissions: Safety at Every Age{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The system grows with your children:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Ages 5-7: Pure Discovery**{{NEWLINE}}- Can only scan, not buy{{NEWLINE}}- Picture-based shopping lists{{NEWLINE}}- Parent pre-approves everything{{NEWLINE}}- Focus on learning and helping{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Ages 8-10: Guided Autonomy**  {{NEWLINE}}- Pre-approved items only{{NEWLINE}}- Small discovery budget{{NEWLINE}}- Gentle nudges toward healthy choices{{NEWLINE}}- Cannot buy harmful products{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Ages 11-13: Real Responsibility**{{NEWLINE}}- Manages actual budget{{NEWLINE}}- Trades tokens with peers{{NEWLINE}}- Learns from mistakes (with safety nets){{NEWLINE}}- Starts helping younger children{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Ages 14+: Full Participation**{{NEWLINE}}- Complete autonomy within family values{{NEWLINE}}- Mentors younger siblings{{NEWLINE}}- Shopping becomes intentional values expression{{NEWLINE}}- Prepares for adult economy{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**For Vulnerable Populations:**{{NEWLINE}}- **Seniors**: Maintains independence longer, prevents duplicate purchases, easy help summoning{{NEWLINE}}- **IDD Community**: Protects from exploitation while enabling autonomy{{NEWLINE}}- **Temporary Vulnerability**: Adjusts during illness, stress, or life transitions{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## The Same Protocol Everywhere{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The revolutionary insight: this protocol works everywhere, not just shopping.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### At the Library{{NEWLINE}}- Scan books while browsing{{NEWLINE}}- Get suggestions based on reading level{{NEWLINE}}- Bundle checkout respects family limits{{NEWLINE}}- Create learning journey stories{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### At the Community Garden{{NEWLINE}}- Scan plants as you harvest{{NEWLINE}}- Ensure fair sharing automatically{{NEWLINE}}- Bundle creates harvest story{{NEWLINE}}- Earn community participation tokens{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### At Home with Chores{{NEWLINE}}- Scan chore card to claim{{NEWLINE}}- Receive guided instructions{{NEWLINE}}- Bundle completion with siblings{{NEWLINE}}- Make family contribution visible{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### At School{{NEWLINE}}- Scan homework when complete{{NEWLINE}}- Trade study tokens with classmates{{NEWLINE}}- Bundle weekly achievements{{NEWLINE}}- Connect learning to family stories{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## The Technology: Familiar Yet Revolutionary{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### What Families Need{{NEWLINE}}- **Smartphones** (you already have){{NEWLINE}}- **Home Hub** ($150 or free via community program){{NEWLINE}}- **Kid Scanner** (optional $30 device for phoneless children){{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### What Stores Need{{NEWLINE}}- **Free Elohim node software** (installs in minutes){{NEWLINE}}- **QR codes on shelves** (like existing price tags){{NEWLINE}}- **Standard QR payment acceptance** (already have){{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### What Makes It Revolutionary{{NEWLINE}}- **No surveillance**: Cameras see but don{{QUOTE}}t record{{NEWLINE}}- **Local-first**: Your data never leaves your home{{NEWLINE}}- **Interoperable**: Works with existing systems{{NEWLINE}}- **Values-aligned**: Care matters as much as cash{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Watch Tommy Shop: The Demo That Changes Minds{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Imagine a split screen showing four perspectives simultaneously:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}'});
CREATE (:ContentChunk {id: 'value-scanner-epic__chunk_1', parentId: 'value-scanner-epic', chunkIndex: 1, totalChunks: 2, content: '**Tommy{{QUOTE}}s View**: His phone showing gentle nudges, discovery suggestions, and care bonuses as he shops.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Family View**: Real-time mission progress, budget tracking, and values being created.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Store View**: Anonymous demand patterns, inventory optimization, and community preferences.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Community View**: Local economy flows, care networks activating, and sustainability metrics improving.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}All from one child buying strawberries for his sister.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This demo doesn{{QUOTE}}t just show an app—it reveals an entirely different economic logic operating inside familiar activities.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Why This Wins{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Against Current Kids{{QUOTE}} Banking{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Them**: $5-15 monthly fees, consumption training, data extraction, corporate lock-in{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**EVS**: Free forever, care cultivation, family sovereignty, community ownership{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### The Subsumption Strategy{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}We{{QUOTE}}re not destroying the old economy. We{{QUOTE}}re growing the new one inside it:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}1. **Near-term**: Replaces kids{{QUOTE}} banking apps and allowance systems{{NEWLINE}}2. **Mid-term**: Integrates with food assistance, school programs, libraries{{NEWLINE}}3. **Long-term**: Makes credit cards, loyalty programs, and data brokers obsolete{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The genius: it uses their infrastructure (stores, phones, QR codes) with our values (care, learning, community).{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### The Network Effects{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Every family that joins strengthens everyone:{{NEWLINE}}- More stores participate{{NEWLINE}}- More patterns emerge{{NEWLINE}}- More care becomes visible{{NEWLINE}}- More value flows locally{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Start Tomorrow: The Family Pilot Program{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Week 1: Your First Day{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Morning:**{{NEWLINE}}- Install app on phones (10 minutes){{NEWLINE}}- Set up kitchen hub{{NEWLINE}}- Define family values together{{NEWLINE}}- Create first shopping missions{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Afternoon:**{{NEWLINE}}- Kids try first solo shopping{{NEWLINE}}- Parents watch stress evaporate{{NEWLINE}}- Stories start accumulating{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Evening:**{{NEWLINE}}- Celebrate the day{{QUOTE}}s contributions{{NEWLINE}}- No fights about chores{{NEWLINE}}- Connection without coordination{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Month 1: The Neighborhood Effect{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}- 5 stores accepting EVS{{NEWLINE}}- 20 families coordinating naturally{{NEWLINE}}- Carpool networks self-organizing{{NEWLINE}}- Local farms thriving{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}### Year 1: The Parallel Economy{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}- Schools issue learning tokens{{NEWLINE}}- Libraries accept care tokens{{NEWLINE}}- Transit rewards community service{{NEWLINE}}- The old economy seems primitive{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## Community Patterns Without Surveillance{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The community sees anonymous patterns that benefit everyone:{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**This Week in Parker Neighborhood:**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Food Patterns:**{{NEWLINE}}- 73% choosing local produce{{NEWLINE}}- Kids discovering: Dragon fruit, bok choy, kumquats{{NEWLINE}}- Unmet demand: Bulk grains, ethnic ingredients{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Care Patterns:**{{NEWLINE}}- 847 elder assistance hours{{NEWLINE}}- 234 childcare swaps{{NEWLINE}}- Tuesday evenings need coverage{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Economic Flows:**{{NEWLINE}}- $47,000 stayed local{{NEWLINE}}- 2,400 hours saved via coordination{{NEWLINE}}- 34 tons CO₂ prevented{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}No individual data. No surveillance. Just patterns that help businesses serve and families thrive.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}## From Strawberries to System Change{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}Remember Tommy in the produce aisle, scanning strawberries for Emma?{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}That simple act contains everything:{{NEWLINE}}- A child learning that thinking of others creates value{{NEWLINE}}- A family coordinating without conflict{{NEWLINE}}- A store supporting local farms{{NEWLINE}}- A community seeing its patterns{{NEWLINE}}- An economy recognizing care{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}This isn{{QUOTE}}t disruption—it{{QUOTE}}s growth. Every family that joins makes the network stronger. Every store that accepts makes it more real. Every child who learns care over consumption shapes the future.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The technology exists today. The Elohim agents are ready to serve. The infrastructure is waiting.{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}The only question is: **When does your family begin writing its story?**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}*Join the revolution that starts with strawberries.*{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**The Elohim Family Pilot Program**  {{NEWLINE}}*No fees. No surveillance. Just care made visible, valuable, and viral.*{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}**Start your family{{QUOTE}}s story at: elohim.host/families**{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}---{{NEWLINE}}{{NEWLINE}}*{{DQUOTE}}The future isn{{QUOTE}}t about the technology we build. It{{QUOTE}}s about the values we encode into it. Today, we choose care.{{DQUOTE}}*'});
